org.cast.cwm.xml
Class XmlDocument

java.lang.Object
  org.cast.cwm.xml.XmlDocument
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<XmlDocument>
public class XmlDocument
extends Object
implements Serializable, Comparable<XmlDocument>

A class that parses and holds the high level structure of an XML document. Also, maintains a static map of all parsed documents.

getLastModified

public org.apache.wicket.util.time.Time getLastModified()
Check and return the last modified time, updating the in-memory data if file has been modified. To avoid constantly reading the disk, this will only actually check based on XmlService's updateCheckInterval, otherwise returning the remembered value.

updateIfModified

protected void updateIfModified()
Check the disk (or DAV server, etc) to see if underlying file has been modified. If so, update the XMLDocument.

getByLabel

public XmlSection getByLabel(Serializable label,
                             Integer num)
Get an XmlSection from this book by its label and count within the book. Applications must override XmlSection#getLabel() for this to function properly.

Parameters:
label - a label as defined by XmlSection#getLabel()
num - specifying the nth instance of this labeled section in the book
Returns:
the matching XmlSection, or null if not found.

getLabelIndex

public int getLabelIndex(Serializable label,
                         XmlSection sec)
Given an XmlSection with a particular label, return its position within the list of all elements with that label (0-based). In other words, returns the number of similarly-labeled elements that precede it.

Parameters:
label -
sec -
Returns:
the index, or -1 if the element was not found or does not itself have the given label.
